# Module 2.3: Review – The Evolution of Cybersecurity

## Overview

This section reviews the key concepts covered in Module 2 and reinforces your understanding of how cybersecurity has evolved over time.

## Glossary Terms

Important terms to remember:

- Malware  
- Phishing  
- Ransomware  
- Vulnerability  
- Threat  
- Risk  
- Denial-of-Service (DoS)  

## Module 2 Challenge

By the end of this module, you should be able to:

- Explain how cybersecurity evolved  
- Identify different types of cyberattacks  
- Understand attacker motivations  
- Recognize the eight CISSP security domains  
- Match attacks to their characteristics  

## Key Takeaways

- Cybersecurity developed as technology evolved  
- Modern attacks are more advanced, organized, and targeted  
- Humans are often the weakest link in security  
- The CISSP domains provide a complete framework for understanding cybersecurity  

## Big Picture

Cybersecurity is a constantly evolving field. As technology advances, new threats emerge, requiring continuous improvement in security strategies and defenses.

## Real-World Application

These concepts are applied in real-world scenarios such as:

- Analyzing attack patterns to improve system defenses  
- Identifying vulnerabilities before attackers exploit them  
- Responding to incidents using structured processes  
- Applying security frameworks to protect organizations 
